Data Sources: 
I used wind capacity factors from Renewables.ninja (DK2 region, 2024) 
and retrieved day-ahead spot prices directly from the Energi Data Service (Energinet) API.
###
   In the refered website 
   "https://data.nordpoolgroup.com/auction/day-ahead/prices?deliveryDate=latest&currency=EUR&aggregation=Hourly&deliveryAreas=AT",
   It seems like you need subscribe before you can download the data excel tables, so here I use data from Energinet.
   If you access the data from the above website, feel free to modify. OWO
###

Scenario Reduction (K-Means):
Instead of random sampling, I used K-Means clustering to extract 20 representative daily profiles for both wind and prices. 
This captures the full distribution of market volatility, including price spikes and extreme wind conditions, 
more effectively than blind sampling.
###
   Here I output figures to show which dates are chosen (those colorful waves) comparing with normal dates (grey waves), 
   both for wind_gene and day-ahead price.
###

Scaling & Probabilities:
The wind data is scaled to our required 500 MW capacity. 
I also calculated the true probabilities for each cluster based on their historical frequency in 2024 (Cardinality/366).
The line "Cluster_ID" can be seen as weight of each scenarios.

Joint Scenarios:
I performed a Cartesian product of the 20 wind scenarios, 20 price scenarios, and 4 randomly generated System Imbalance (SI) states. 
This resulted in a final set of 1,600 joint scenarios, each with a specific joint probability and 
calculated Balancing Price (BP): 
   Calculate BP based on assignment rules:
   If SI=1 (deficit), BP = 1.25 * DA price
   If SI=0 (surplus), BP = 0.85 * DA price

Output: 
The final input file for our optimization model is "final_1600_scenarios_input.csv". 
It contains 38,400 rows (1600 scenarios × 24 hours)
